OL,6,FMr Hoath, who had split up with the
OL,7,Fdefendant, added that he was
OL,8,F"devastated" and his world had been
OL,9,Fturned "upside down" by the loss of
OL,10,Fhis "young, boisterous lads".
OL,12,FGreat-grandmother Sally Johnson wept
OL,13,Fin court as she described the "horror"
OL,14,Fand "pain" of her loss.
OL,16,FShe said: "The thought of them crying
OL,17,Fand screaming out for help will haunt
OL,18,Fme forever. How frightened and scared
OL,19,Fthey must have been, although
OL,20,Ftogether, still alone.
